platform: ios
engine: v3.7 js-binding

when I exit the game, call the following code (same as the demo of cpp-helloworld click close menu item)

```
    Director::getInstance()->end();
#if (CC_TARGET_PLATFORM == CC_PLATFORM_IOS)
    exit(0);
#endif
```

allways crash at ScriptingCore::cleanup:

```
    for (auto iter = _js_global_type_map.begin(); iter != _js_global_type_map.end(); ++iter)
    {
        CCLOG("typeName = %s", iter->first.c_str());
        free(iter->second->jsclass);  //  EXC_BAD_ACCESS
        free(iter->second);
    }
```

I try to find where freed `iter->second->jsclass` before `ScriptingCore::cleanup`, but not found.
why crash at this code, please tell me if you known, thanks.

fixed ActionManager memory leak
when I create a node with an action, and not add to any other node, such as:

```
var sp = cc.Sprite.create("text.png");
sp.runAction(cc.fadeOut(10));
//has not parent
```

This will lead to memory leak, in correctly, 'sp' will be released in next frame, but when it run an action, 'sp' will not be released forever.
